.TH "cma_init_reserved_mem" 9 "cma_init_reserved_mem" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cma_init_reserved_mem \- create custom contiguous area from reserved memory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cma_init_reserved_mem
.BI "(phys_addr_t base "  ","
.BI "phys_addr_t size "  ","
.BI "unsigned int order_per_bit "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "struct cma **res_cma "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "base" 12
Base address of the reserved area
.IP "size" 12
Size of the reserved area (in bytes),
.IP "order_per_bit" 12
Order of pages represented by one bit on bitmap.
.IP "name" 12
The name of the area. If this parameter is NULL, the name of
the area will be set to "cmaN", where N is a running counter of
used areas.
.IP "res_cma" 12
Pointer to store the created cma region.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function creates custom contiguous area from already reserved memory.
